# .trivyignore — the accepted-risk register for image scanning (Phase 5, D15).
#
# POLICY: the 13 mirrored images are FROZEN 2017-2018 upstream pins (D5/D6/D8) —
# their CVE sets are known, accepted, and documented here and in docs/. Scanning
# them is still valuable as a MANIFEST of accepted risk (and Trivy under-reports
# on EOL bases — a low score on an EOL image is blindness, not cleanliness).
# Blocking applies to anything NEW: the pipeline's scan-gate job demonstrates
# CRITICAL-blocking, and any future non-legacy image goes through it.
#
# Mitigations that make these acceptable FOR THIS DEMO (not for production):
#   - private subnets, no public IPs, least-privilege SG chain (only the ALB
#     faces the internet, and only front-end receives from it)
#   - images served from OUR registry (no upstream drift after mirror)
#   - ephemeral data tier; RDS is the only persistent store
# Production path: current base images (rebuild the 2017 apps), DocumentDB/
# Amazon MQ/ElastiCache managed replacements, WAF on the ALB. See docs.
#
# Harvested CRITICAL examples (mirror job logs, 2026-07-05) — carts:0.4.8:
# os: alpine 3.4.6 (EOL)
CVE-2017-8105
CVE-2017-8287
CVE-2016-9841
CVE-2016-9843
